The paper discusses the development of a practical multilayer time-based spiking neuromorphic architecture for efficient neural processing and classification accuracy. This work involves the use of deep learning techniques such as DNN and CNN, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper focuses on recognition tasks, which are often associated with the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Finally, the paper discusses the implementation of the architecture on resource-limited platforms, which falls under the sub-category of cs.ET (Embedded Systems).
